on, I am bound not only to regard them with <HI>chri&s;tian charity;</HI> but al&s;o (after &s;o &s;evere a cen&s;ure of their profe&s;&s;ion in general) freely to declare, that there are many, very many, <HI>individuals</HI> among them, who&s;e various good qualities and virtues ju&s;tly entitle them to my &s;incere e&s;teem and re&s;pect; to &s;uch, therefore, I can only add in the words of the Scripture&mdash;<Q><HI>Come out of her, my people,</HI></Q> (i. e. all ye that <HI>fear God;</HI> and the more e&s;pecially as the period of her power, the com|pletion of the 1260 years of <HI>Roman</HI> tyranny, ve&s;ted in ten, or rather eleven, crowned Horns, is probably not far di&s;tant; all the <HI>prophetical marks</HI> of her apo&s;tacy being evident &s;o early as about the middle of the 6th <Q>cen|tury,) <HI>that ye be not partakers of her &s;ins, and that ye receive not of her plagues. For her</HI> SIN <HI>hath reached unto Heaven, and God hath remembered her</HI> INIQUI|TIES!</Q> Rev. xviii. 4.5.</NOTE>
